 might be more redshifted if larger transition-region downflows\nare present. We also find that the observed average Ly-b profile is redshifted\nwith respect to its rest position.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 6 Jul 2009 18:42:08 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-09-10"}
